        "avatar_template": "https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/8edcca/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2021-06-28T15:09:30.519Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"markus.pilman\" data-post=\"7\" data-topic=\"2461\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://sea1.discourse-cdn.com/foundationdb/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/markus.pilman/48/379_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> markus.pilman:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>We\u2019re currently working on FDB on ARM Linux (which is mostly working already but not officially supported yet as we still need to build test infrastructure).</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>That\u2019s good! The needs of my team are to be able to run FoundationDB inside a kubernetes cluster (either on the cloud or locally inside k3d), in Linux docker images. My understanding is that a working FoundationDB ARM64 build on linux would allow such deployment scenario even on M1. Correct me if I am wrong.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"markus.pilman\" data-post=\"7\" data-topic=\"2461\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://sea1.discourse-cdn.com/foundationdb/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/markus.pilman/48/379_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> markus.pilman:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>most FDB developers don\u2019t have access to M1 Macs</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>In fact, I was more referring to a potential, M2/M1X evolution of the M1 where the ARM64 will start to be interesting for development purpose (more memory, etc\u2026). From this point, I think a properly working Linux ARM64 FoundationDB build would be quite welcome <img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/wink.png?v=12\" title=\":wink:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":wink:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"markus.pilman\" data-post=\"7\" data-topic=\"2461\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://sea1.discourse-cdn.com/foundationdb/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/markus.pilman/48/379_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> markus.pilman:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>we would be more than happy to accept pull requests</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Would be happy to contribute! (more on the Record Layer though since it\u2019s the code base I am more familiar with\u2026)</p>",
